  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nUser initiated a test archive session and used session-navigator to view the Notion archive structure. A fusion operation was performed to consolidate three duplicate 'Export Session vers Notion' entries into a single master session. The fusion successfully created a master record in Notion Memory Hub and marked the source sessions as archived.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nTesting archive attendance and managing session duplicates through the session-navigator skill\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nExecuted session-navigator to display archive structure, identified duplicate sessions, performed fusion operation to create master session, and archived source duplicates\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [session-navigator] Archive Structure Display — Comprehensive view of 17 pages across 4 categories in Notion\n- [master-session] MASTER SESSION — Export Session vers Notion (Fusion x3) — Consolidated session in Notion Memory Hub with high priority status\n- [archive-update] Source Session Archiving — Three duplicate sessions marked as archived in Notion\n\n## Key Decisions & Validations\n\n- Execute fusion of duplicate sessions instead of manual cleanup\n- Create master session in Memory Hub with high priority\n- Archive source sessions to prevent future duplicates\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- Session-navigator provided clear overview of archive structure\n- Fusion operation executed cleanly with proper Notion integration\n- Automatic duplicate detection and consolidation workflow\nDiscoveries:\n\n- Archive contains 17 pages across 4 categories\n- Duplicate detection capabilities within session-navigator\n- Master session creation maintains links to source materials\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Monitor master session for completeness\n- Consider renaming non-standard entries like 'Article' and 'New Entry'\n- Evaluate need for additional fusion operations\n---\nUID: EdUHTwnqlM3zJVWkenqEe8 | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0155\n"
}